      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "Kabbalat Shabbat, \"Welcoming Shabbat,\" is one of the ritual innovations of the\ncircle of Kabbalists (Jewish mystics) who gathered around Rabbi Isaac Luria in sixteenth-century\nSafed in the Land of Israel.\nPsalms 95-99, 29 — This cycle of six psalms, representing the six days of creation, enjoins all\ncreation to sing out the praises of God. God's creative power is revealed in the world around us;\nGod's sovereignty is over all nature and all nations.",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
